/wiki/Ghader_Mizbani: Ghader Mizbani Iranagh (Persian: قادر میزبانی ایرانق‎, born 6 September 1975 in Tabriz) is an Iranian former professional road bicycle racer, who rode professionally between 2001 and 2018 for the Telekom Malaysia Cycling Team, the Giant Asia Racing Team, Brisaspor, the Tabriz Petrochemical Team and the Tabriz Shahrdary Team. Mizbani won the overall standings of the UCI Asia Tour twice – in 2005–06 and 2008–09. Mizbani won the Iranian National Road Race Championships three times and the Iranian National Time Trial Championships twice.
/wiki/Cycling_at_the_1998_Asian_Games: Cycling was contested at the 1998 Asian Games in Thailand from December 7 to December 19. Road bicycle racing was held at the Highway No 1 and No 2 from Saraburi Province to Nakhon Ratchasima Province, while track cycling was contested at Huamark Velodrome in Bangkok and mountain biking was contested in Khao Yai National Park, Nakhon Ratchasima Province.
/wiki/Behzad_Gholampour: Behzad Gholampour (Persian: بهزاد غلامپور‎; born December 23, 1966) is a retired Iranian football and futsal goalkeeper. He was the goalkeeping trainer for Iran national football team from 2008 until late March 2009.
/wiki/Nima_Nakisa: Nima Nakisa (Persian: نیما نکیسا‎, born May 1, 1975 in Tehran) is an Iranian Singer and retired football goalkeeper.
/wiki/Hamid_Reza_Babaei: Hamidreza Babaei (born April 22, 1975) is an Iranian footballer. He currently plays for Esteghlal Ahvaz F.C. in the IPL.
/wiki/Nader_Mohammadkhani: Nader Mohammadkhani (Persian: نادر محمدخانی‎, born August 23, 1963 in Tehran) is a retired Iranian football player.
/wiki/Javad_Zarrincheh: Javad Zarincheh (Persian: جواد زرینچه‎, born July 23, 1966 in Tehran) is a former Iranian football player, coach and a football administrator. He is currently team manager of Esteghlal. He played for the Iran national football team and was a participant at the 1998 FIFA World Cup.
/wiki/Mohammad_Khakpour: Mohammad Khakpour (Persian: محمد خاکپور‎, born February 20, 1969) is a retired Iranian football player.
/wiki/Mohammad_Navazi: Mohamad Navazi (Persian: محمد نوازی‎, born September 5, 1974) is a Retired Iranian football player who mostly played for Esteghlal Tehran, He usually played as a Right Midfielder.
/wiki/Sattar_Hamedani: Sattar Hamedani (Persian: ستار همدانی‎) born 6 June 1974 in Tabriz) is a retired Iranian football player. He usually played in the midfielder position.
/wiki/Ali_Karimi: Ali Karimi (Persian: علی کریمی‎ Persian: [ɑli kæriˈmi] (listen); born 8 November 1978) is an Iranian football coach and retired player. He has played for Fath Tehran, Persepolis, Al-Ahli Dubai, Bayern Munich, Qatar SC, Steel Azin, Schalke 04, Tractor Sazi, and the Iran national team for which he scored 38 goals in 127 appearances. In 2004, he became the fourth Iranian player to win the Asian Footballer of the Year. He announced his retirement at the end of the 2013–14 season and, on 11 April 2014, played the final game of his 18-year career.
/wiki/Dariush_Yazdani: Dariush Yazdani (Persian: داریوش یزدانی‎; born June 2, 1977) is an Iranian former footballer who played as a midfielder.
/wiki/Mahmoud_Fekri: Mahmoud Fekri Juybari (born July 26, 1969 in Juybar, Iran) is a former Iranian football player who is currently head coach of Shahin Bushehr in Azadegan League. He was previously head coach of Shirin Faraz in the Iran Pro League and assistant coach of Esteghlal and Saba Qom. He usually played the defender position.
/wiki/Alireza_Mansourian: Alireza Mansourian (Persian: علیرضا منصوريان‎, born 2 December 1971) is an Iranian football coach and retired player.
/wiki/Ali_Mousavi: This article is about the football player Ali Mousavi.  For the article on the death of the nephew of Iranian opposition leader Mir Hossein Mousavi, see: Death of Seyed Ali Mousavi.
/wiki/Vahid_Hashemian: Vahid Hashemian (Persian: وحيد هاشميان‎, born 21 July 1976) is a retired Iranian football striker and current coach who is currently assistant to Marc Wilmots at Iran national football team.
/wiki/Mehdi_Mahdavikia: Mehdi Mahdavikia (Persian: مهدی مهدوی‌کیا (help·info)‎, born 24 July 1977) is an Iranian professional football coach and former player usually played as a right winger or full-back.
/wiki/Ali_Daei: Ali Daei (Persian: علی دایی (help·info)‎ pronounced [ʔæliː dɑːjiː]; born 21 March 1969) is an Iranian former professional footballer, football manager and businessman. A striker, he was captain of the Iran national football team, and played for clubs such as Bayern Munich and Hertha BSC. He is currently the owner and CEO of Daei Sport.
/wiki/Karim_Bagheri: Karim Bagheri (Persian: کريم باقری (help·info)‎; born 20 February 1974) is a retired Iranian professional football player and coach. He played over half of his professional career for Persepolis in the Persian Gulf Pro League.
/wiki/Rasoul_Khatibi: Rasoul Khatibi (Persian: رسول خطیبی‎, born 22 September 1978) is an Iranian former footballer and coach who currently manages Azadegan League team Aluminium Arak. He is the younger brother of Hossein Khatibi, who is also a football manager.
/wiki/Hamid_Estili: Hamid Reza Estili (Persian: حميد استيلی‎, born 1 April 1967) is an Iranian football coach and retired player. He is currently the manager of the Iran national under-23 team. Estili was a member of the Iran national team and is mostly remembered for his memorable goal and goal celebration against USA at the 1998 FIFA World Cup.
/wiki/Football_at_the_1998_Asian_Games: Football at the 1998 Asian Games was held in Thailand from 30 November to 19 December 1998.
/wiki/Alireza_Katiraei: Alireza Katiraei, (Persian: علیرضا کتیرایی‎, born March 5, 1976 in Qom), is an entired professional Iranian karateka. Katiraei won gold medal in 1998 Asian Games and 2002 Asian Games.
/wiki/Karate_at_the_1998_Asian_Games: Karate was competed by men and women at the 1998 Asian Games in Rangsit Sports Complex, Bangkok, Thailand. Kata was contested along with Kumite. There were 11 gold medals contested for this sport. All competition took place on December 15, 16 and 17.
/wiki/Taekwondo_at_the_1998_Asian_Games: Taekwondo took place from December 7 to December 10 at the 1998 Asian Games in Thammasat University, Gymnasium 7, Bangkok, Thailand. Each country (except the host nation) was limited to having 6 men and 6 women for the entire competition.
/wiki/Shahin_Nassirinia: Shahin Nassirinia (Persian: شاهین نصیری‌نیا‎, born February 25, 1976 in Shiraz) is an Iranian weightlifter who won the gold medal in the Men's 85 kg weight class at the 1999 World Weightlifting Championships. He participated in the 2000 Sydney Olympics but got injured in the first attempt at Snatch lift.
/wiki/Weightlifting_at_the_1998_Asian_Ga: Weightlifting contested from December 7 to December 14 at the  1998 Asian Games in Bangkok Land Sports Complex, Bangkok, Thailand.
/wiki/Amir_Tavakkolian: Amir Tavakkolian (Persian: امیر توکلیان‎, born 7 September 1971 in Mashhad) is an Iranian wrestler.
/wiki/Wrestling_at_the_1998_Asian_Games: Wrestling was one of the many sports which was held at the 1998 Asian Games in Bangkok, Thailand between 12 and 18 December 1998. The competition took place at Thammasat Gymnasium 1.
/wiki/Wrestling_at_the_1998_Asian_Games_: The men's freestyle 69 kg wrestling competition at the 1998 Asian Games in Bangkok was held on 17 December and 18 December at the Thammasat Gymnasium 1.
/wiki/Alireza_Heidari: Alireza Heidari (Persian: علیرضا حیدری‎, born March 4, 1976 in Tehran) is a retired Iranian wrestler who competed in the Men's Freestyle 96 kg at the 2004 Summer Olympics and won the bronze medal.
/wiki/Wrestling_at_the_1998_Asian_Games_: The men's freestyle 85 kg wrestling competition at the 1998 Asian Games in Bangkok was held on 17 December and 18 December at the Thammasat Gymnasium 1.
/wiki/Abbas_Jadidi: Abbas Jadidi (Persian: عباس جدیدی‎, born January 13, 1969, in Tehran) is an Iranian wrestler who competed in the Freestyle Heavyweight (90–100 kg) category at the 1996 Summer Olympics, losing to Kurt Angle and winning the silver medal. He was suspended from competing for two years for doping. He was elected as a member of Tehran City Council in 2013 local elections.
/wiki/Wrestling_at_the_1998_Asian_Games_: The men's freestyle 97 kg wrestling competition at the 1998 Asian Games in Bangkok was held on 16 December and 17 December at the Thammasat Gymnasium 1.
/wiki/Alireza_Rezaei: Alireza Rezaei (Persian: علیرضا رضایی‎, born July 11, 1976) is a former Iranian wrestler who competed in the Men's Freestyle 120 kg at the 2004 Summer Olympics and won the silver medal. He is currently Executive director of Iranian national team.
/wiki/Wrestling_at_the_1998_Asian_Games_: The men's freestyle 130 kg wrestling competition at the 1998 Asian Games in Bangkok was held on 17 December and 18 December at the Thammasat Gymnasium 1.
The men's Greco-Roman 130 kg wrestling competition at the 1998 Asian Games in Bangkok was held on 13 December and 14 December at the Thammasat Gymnasium 1.
/wiki/Hamid_Sajjadi: Seyed Hamid Sajjadi Hazaveh (Persian: سید حمید سجادی هزاوه‎, born 21 March 1969) is an Iranian retired middle distance and long distance runner. He represented Iran at the 1992 Summer Olympics and 1996 Summer Olympics. Sajjadi holds multiple indoor and outdoor national track records for Iran.[citation needed]
/wiki/Athletics_at_the_1998_Asian_Games: The athletics competition at the 1998 Asian Games were held in Bangkok, Thailand between 13 and 20 December.
/wiki/Mohammad_Reza_Samadi: Mohammad Reza Samadi Kalkhoran (Persian: محمدرضا صمدی کلخوران‎; born 1 January 1971) is a retired amateur boxer from Iran, who competed in the 1996 Summer Olympics in the Super heavyweight (+91 kg) division and lost in the first round to Duncan Dokiwari of Nigeria. He is also a two time Asian Games silver medalist.
/wiki/Boxing_at_the_1998_Asian_Games: The Boxing Tournament at the 1998 Asian Games was held at the IMPACT Arena in Bangkok, Thailand from 7 December to 18 December 1998.
/wiki/Mahmoud_Miran: Mahmoud Reza Miran Fashandi (Persian: سید محمودرضا میران فشندی‎, born February 25, 1974) more known as Mahmoud Miran was an Iranian judoka.
/wiki/Judo_at_the_1998_Asian_Games: The Judo competition at the 1998 Asian Games was contested in fourteen weight classes, seven each for men and women, held at the Thammasat University in Thailand.
/wiki/Majid_Aflaki: Majid Aflaki (born 26 August 1973) is an Iranian taekwondo practitioner. He competed in the 2000 Summer Olympics.
/wiki/Mohammad_Hossein_Barkhah: Mohammad Hossein Barkhah (Persian: محمد حسین برخواه‎, born 24 January 1977 in Tehran) is a retired Iranian weightlifting champion. In 2003, while in Vancouver, Canada, at a competition, he twisted one of his arms while performing a snatch. He represented the Islamic Republic of Iran in weightlifting in both the 2000 and 2004 Olympics.
/wiki/Kourosh_Bagheri:
Kourosh Bagheri (Persian: كوروش باقری‎, born 21 September 1977 in Kermanshah) is a former Iranian weightlifter who won the gold medal in the Men's 94 kg weight class at the 2001 World Weightlifting Championships.
Bagheri was also holding the Asian Record of Snatch in 94 kg at the 2000 Summer Olympics in Sydney, as well as the Asian Record of Total in 94 kg at the 2001 World Weightlifting Championships.  
He was the head coach of Iran's weightlifting team at London Olympics in summer 2012 in which he coached Iranian weightlifters who won 2 Gold and 3 Silver medals.
/wiki/Behnam_Tayyebi: Behnam Tayyebi Kermani (Persian: بهنام طیبی کرمانی‎, born 23 July 1975 in Qaem Shahr) is a retired Iranian wrestler. He competed at the 2000 Summer Olympics in Sydney, in the men's freestyle 54 kg.
/wiki/Wrestling_at_the_1998_Asian_Games_: The men's freestyle 54 kg wrestling competition at the 1998 Asian Games in Bangkok was held on 16 December and 17 December at the Thammasat Gymnasium 1.
